annotation.TEXT: Hmm... This area took a few seconds to load.
Alright, so world 2 on the Easy side is completed!
Goal tape average so far: 456 / 13 = 35.077 stars each.
Bah! I forgot about those!

A dark underground extends down in the basement of this castle. The path onward can be opened through switching between On and Off. However, your journey will also be filled with traps. This castle also has supposedly-invincible Black Birdos.

Beyond is a deadly elevator up to Rumia's room! There's a three-HP system in place, but deadly Bullet Bills will attack Mario! Get Rumia to run into the flames thrice and she'll be defeated! Rumia: "Is it okay if I eat yooou?"
Yeah, I could play MariYOLO Adventure fairly, but I'd either die very early on, or I'd just take the easy way out.
Okay, this is my stop.
Didn't see anything up there, but I did manage to defeat that Chuck with a dive bomb quake.
Ow, brain my!
Okay, so we've got Super Mario All-Stars graphics, complete with the background. Except, the portrait is of Rumia instead of Bowser. (However, the statues are still of Bowser.)
Uh, oh. If Rumia's ribbon came off, that's probably not a good thing...
It's getting dark! And there's no light! (° v °) Not to mention that's quite the auto-scroll... Waha! - Rumia
Whoa, outta the way, stupid Koopa!
Oh, nice. Just like that, I'm back up to full power. (Too bad reaching full power doesn't automatically cancel out all bullets on the screen here, like it does in certain Touhou games.)
Ditto for these pipes.
Meh. Forget it. (Oh, BTW, I do notice that the ON/OFF blocks briefly look like Pokey heads as I'm hitting them, so there's no need to mention that in the comments.)
Darkness
Okay, this is a good place for me to make use of my reserve feather.
Zwee!
Mario sunk Castle Rumia, conquering World 2! World 3 is ruled by the ice fairy Cirno, who's a moronic... I mean, it's a world of harsh winter! By the way, Rumia's ribbon came off... "Waha!"
Come on, Rumia. Hit the flame already.
Umm... How would I get that? Maybe if this is a Lay's Wavy Eerie cannon...
Hello, and welcome back to Scarlet Devil Mario! Let's not waste any time and get straight to the voting results...
Ooh, that unlocked a little shortcut on the map here, which'll save me a few seconds whenever I want to come this way.
Yeah, I'm kinda dancing to the music when I've got nothing better to do while waiting.
It's kinda strange how Boos seem to aim for a position just above your head when you look away.
Oh, man. That level name. I wonder if it'll be an automatic level, allowing me to clear it without moving... Nah, probably not.
Good thing I have a cape to help me with these jumps.
Oookaaay, those spherical objects hurt. Good to know.
Can I cape thwack that Parakoopa from the other side of this switch block wall?
Gotta avoid all the hot stuff and the Rottweiler-Disc. Woof.
Whoops, the game just crashed! ...Wait, this isn't SMBX, which crashes when a moving mushroom hits lava, I think.
As consolation for all these "invisible coinblock" traps, I'll get rid of the fog for you. Waha! - Rumia
Oh, nice! The 3HP system ended, returning me to my former status! Too bad I don't get to keep the cape, but that's okay.
Yep, totally. It would be kind of hard to be more obvious than that.
Oh, man. A potato chip cannon.
Alright, so let's play Dark Ghost House (Normal)!
Ha! I was able to cape thwack Chuck from the other side of the switch blocks.
(Insert dropping sound effect here.)
So, where should I head next? Castle Rumia (Normal), or Icicle Fall (Easy)? Vote now! To be continued... Ze!
Oh, man. An Eerie cannon.

Yep, so that message box removed the layer 3 fog, which wasn't really an issue anyway. (Also, the translation document calls that message box "Kind of hard to reach", but I don't think it's any harder than proceeding normally with the level here.)
Whoa! Oh, yeah! I totally remember this place from raocow's playthrough (probably thanks to the music)!
No, you may not eat me. However, I could find you something else delicious if you want, like cake, perhaps.
Looks like the Bullet Bills always make right-angle turns to the right when they hit a wall, a floor, or one of those spherical objects.
Since I have a cape, is there anything hidden up above?
No Yoshis because even "Easy modo" castles are too hard for them.
That looked like a left turn there, but it was actually three right turns in quick succession.
Okay, so how do I proceed now? Can I get that Lay's Wavy Eerie cannon to fire again? ...Maybe I can just do a sprinting jump to get back over there.
Wow, that was a lot of text. Okay, now this is just a hunch, but I betcha that flashing gold pipe with the coin arrow pointing to it is enterable.
BTW, that house also matches the type of #442 (Spiritomb).
Ooh, now we're getting tricky.
Uh, oh. I only have 1 HP left, so I can't make any more mistakes!
I'm going to try to kill most of the Bullet Bills to reduce the lag.
And Rumia's turned into a door, and the room lit up.
Wow, I did not even see those spikes there. They blended in too well with the background, and my attention was focused on the Thwimp.
Ah, it's this music again.
Finally. Okay, that's two. And I'm guessing the final flame is at the very end of the room.
Okay, so as long as I don't take two more hits, I should be fine.
So, I take it that this is a supposedly-invincible Birdo?
Uh, oh. It's those yellow shrinker stripes, followed immediately by spikes.
Seriously, game? Yeah, these cannons don't respect my proximity.
I guess single coins can also hint at hidden 1-up blocks in addition to hidden coin blocks.
Okay, I was able to check that pipe. Can't enter it.
BGM: VVVVVV - Pushing Onwards
"Tick." Graze +1.
Why did Nintendo make it so the sides of spikes hurt you in SMW, anyway? They don't in SMB2 and SMB3.
Okay, so I've gotta get Rumia to run into the flames thrice.
I'm going to assume that that platform down there is where the midpoint entrance of this level places you.
I guess I can take a peek at world 3...
I'm guessing Porcupo is just a standard Spiny with different graphics.
BGM: Touhou 6 - Rumia's Theme - Apparitions Stalk the Night
I still wonder why Nintendo made Big Boos slide-killable, but not the normal Boos as well... (Trying to slide-kill a normal Boo will only get you hurt.)
Been takin' lessons from Reimu, Mario? I mean, I know I duck-jumped onto the ladder, but I'm still really astonished that that one bullet didn't hit me!
Oh, hey there, cute Big Boo. Hmm... Big Boos don't naturally aim high like the little ones do. Also, I don't think they're shell-killable.
Yes, made it! Okay, let's ride a potato chip to the right again, but this time, don't bounce up to where the message box is.
Umm... I think I'll keep my flower.
Nah, I'm not gonna try to maintain cape flight through the whole level.
Gotta check every pipe, except I'm pretty sure that the pipes with statues on them wouldn't be enterable.
No Yoshis because they're afraid of the dark and ghosts.
BGM: SMB3 - Ice World (World 6) Map
Yeah, he's neither flammable nor inflammable. But, I can still burn his eggs.
Okay, so Rumia said that this is "quite the auto-scroll", but this auto-scroll appears to be set to the slow speed, so I don't think there's much to worry about... maybe.
Yeah, I noticed the timer there, and decided to do that again.
I think there's a potato chip... er, I mean, Eerie generator here.
Oh, but I'm still fiery? ...Right, this level uses a 3HP system. Look up where by bonus stars normally are. It says "HP 2" there now.
Icicle Fall (Easy)
Alright, it's boss time! And, looks like Rumia's taken the role of the Fishing Fish Guy.
This area's graphics remind me of Donkey Kong Country.
Alright, that's every Yoshi coin in this place.
Ah, it is. I hope it's not sour cream and onion. My tongue doesn't like that flavor...

Huh, I suddenly became caped there. Oh, I guess the 3HP system ended right there, reverting me back to the power up status I had before entering this level, and returning the bonus star display back to normal.
No shell-less Koopa? I must've been at the sprite limit.
That's one. So, basically, for the most part, this battle consists of me just avoiding the "Fishing Boo" as I proceed through the room.
Oh, and I just noticed the timer, which means...
Umm... I'm not gonna try to check that pipe. If it is actually enterable, let me know.
Darn it all. I overshot there and didn't move back to the left in time. Well, anyway, there's the last Yoshi coin, and I guess I go into this golden pipe.
Heh. Good thing I checked, because that one could've fallen right on my head.
Note: There's one "pick_random" vote that was made that I didn't list here, because that voter made two "pick_random" votes. I'm not accepting more than one "pick_random" vote per person.

Oh, I can stand up against the left wall to keep the cannon from firing. Why didn't I think of that sooner? (I wouldn't have been able to hug the left wall at all times, but I could've kept some of the bullets from being fired this way earlier.)
To Rumia World (Translation provided by Teradramon Teradramon.)

Okay, so we've once again got the 3HP system going here, but I'm caped this time. Also, there's a bullet cannon in the upper-left that fires special Bullet Bills that change direction when they hit something.
There you go! I've finally remembered to pause during the "Hurry up!" sound effect!
Yeah, I see that Porcupo there. So, I guessing that's what that message box meant by my journey being filled with traps.
Castle Rumia (Normal)
Also, that box held an Eerie cannon. Good thing I wasn't up against the side of the box when it first fired!
Alright, that unlocked the castle on the Normal side, as expected. Now, I think I'll do Castle Rumia (Easy) next. Let me quickly get over there...
Almost screwed up there. Okay, there's the last flame!
Alright, this level is done like dinner. (Which was a microwaved leftover slice of pizza in my case tonight.)
Thank you, adakkusu-san, for removing the F-bomb here!
That would've been silly if I had let that spike embed itself into my brain while I was checking that pipe.
